3》 [with negative] N. Amer. anything at all: you don't know dick about it!
■ verb (usu. dick around/about) informal, chiefly N. Amer. meddle or fool around.

C16 (in the general sense 'fellow'): familiar form of the given name Richard.

early 20th cent.: perh. an arbitrary shortening of detective, or from obs. sl. dick 'look', from Romany.
